controller
Enum Skeleton

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<Skeleton>
      controller.Skeleton
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Skeleton>
public enum Skeleton
extends java.lang.Enum<Skeleton>

An easier to manipulate enum representing the skeletal constants available in the SimpleOpenNIConstants. This enum provided easy selection of left and right side also supports mirroring. It is possible to retrieve all points in a category using getAllLeft(), getAllRight(), getAllCenter().

Author:
Levi Lindsley

mirror

public static java.lang.Integer mirror(java.lang.Integer val)
Locates the opposing side value (left/right) that is contained in the enum values. If val is not represented or if it represents a center value then this returns null.

Parameters:
val - - value to mirror
Returns:
Left/Right mirror of val

null if no mirror-able point is located

See Also:
mirror(Set)

mirror

public static java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer> mirror(java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer> val)
Creates a set of all values from val that could be mirrored OR were found to be single values. This is more efficient that calling mirror(Integer) for each value in the set assuming the set is backed by an efficient look up manner (TreeSet or HashSet for example).

Parameters:
val - - Set to attempt to mirror
Returns:
Set that contains all mirrored values OR single values. Values in val that are not represented by Skeleton are not represented here.
